docs.lead_paragraph: To the Editor of the New-York Daily Times : The columns of your valuable publication has of late shown forth to the American public a frightful mortality among those who have ventured to brave the perils of a sea journey, and seek a home among them. In your remarks on emigration, on the 17th of November, you suggest the necessity of new regulation on board emigrantships.

headline.main: LATER FROM HAVANA.; ARRIVAL OF THE BLACK WARRIOR.

docs.lead_paragraph: The new Captain-General, Pezuela, expected hourly at Havana--Revolting Murder of Matilda Dominguez-Her Husband Condemned to the Garrote. The steamer Black Warrior, I.D. BULLOCK Commander, arrived on Sunday night at this port, from Mobile 25th, Havana 29th.
